      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS BOBBIE (2) jumped cleanly from the rails to lead much the way when second (17.99) at Mt Gambier in a Maiden over 305m. Top prospect. FLYING NARDO (3) is yet to break through in 11 starts but has run a number of placings. Finished sixth (23.84) at Geelong latest but tends to run well here despite having never won. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Should be thereabouts. PAW ULA (6) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.09) at Warrnambool behind Aston Blitz in a Bottom Up - Maiden. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Will give a great sight again. PERFECT GLOSS (1) must be respected despite an unplaced effort here most recently.",
